--- !u!114 &244192735
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 244192731}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ea1c59ace054e0f4cb9e17e1e77a9b89, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueTrigger
  textComponent: {fileID: 0}
  lines:
  - "\"You were not chosen for your strength. You were chosen because you never stopped
    being curious. That hunger \u2014 to learn, to reach toward what you do not yet
    know \u2014 that is the rarest thing a living soul can carry. It is what I look
    for. It is what I wait for.\""
  - "\"But I died. Whatever I was \u2014 it was already gone before I woke here.\""
  - "\"Yes. The busy world wore you down. The passion faded. That is how that part
    of a person dies \u2014 not in battle. Quietly. From forgetting. But it never
    dies completely. It only sleeps, within you.\""
  - '"And yet you woke it again. Every time you drew something new. Every friend
    you helped. Every thing you chose to learn simply because it interested you.
    That is all it has ever been."'
  - "The warmth faded. The sun moved again. Dusk resumed.  The pen gave one final
    pulse \u2014 and the glow was gone. Then the pen faded, back into golden sand."
  - Nesia closed her fingers gently. Then she took a sit on the temple's steps and
    felt, for the first time since her resurrection, completely whole.
  - After a while, she stood, leaving the valuable artifacts behind. No sword. No
    coin.
  - "She had herself, her memories, with her burning passion. And the long road home
    \u2014 which was, she supposed, just another kind of beginning."
  - Keeping those thoughts in mind, she slowly walked into the dusk, into her new
    start.
  - The end.
  textSpeed: 0.05
  playerTag: Player
  triggerOnce: 1
